<br>
80% or more of the bards I know very rarely if ever equip an instrument during combat.  Therefore, they are a primary melee class, whether they are as effective as possible that way or not.  I wasn't trying to start an argument based on how many drops each class gets, or whether double attack is better than duel wield or not.<br>
<br>
I have a CoF.  I won it because I rolled on it at a Ragefire raid.  Most of the tanks there decided they wanted to roll on the Blazing BP of Fennin Ro, even though it was inferior to the BPs they already had.  I decided to roll on an item when it would benefit another class much more, I had no problem with my rolling on an item that would benefit them more. &lt;shrug&gt;  Cut and dry.  Personally don't care whether &gt;I&lt; am allowed to roll or not, since I already have one, and in fact on most of the dragon raids I've run due to popular demand (by tanks) the CoF has not been open to bards.<br>
<br>
Bish asked for opinions.  That's mine.  Some bards are an exception.  A CoF wouldn't do much good at all for Raventod, Waladen, Yansabar, several other bards I could mention.  They spend over 50 percent of their time with instruments equipped.  Just as it doesn't REALLY do much good for me, although the extra haste is nice as I dual wield weapons that proc stuns when I'm melee'ing.  Thx Skean and Harmonic Dagger.  But by and large the majority of the bards I see out there equip instruments during downtime only... and therefore, are melee'ing the entire time during combat.<br>
<br>
But yeah, I do agree with you.  Bards IDEALLY shouldn't be rolling on the CoF if they're playing their class in the most effective manner possible.  They'll be swapping in and out of instruments and weapons during combat depending on what songs they're using, and the Cloak won't be giving them haste the whole time like it would a tank.  Unfortunately not all bards play to the utmost abilities of their class. &lt;shrug&gt;<br>
<br>
Flarestar Bladesinger <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucowardlymonk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cowardly Monk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dervish Cutthroat</span><br>  Posts: 170<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/6/01 6:45:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=796.topic&index=87>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dragon loot - opinions please.</span><hr size=1> Just thought I would /bump this.  I think this was a very good treatise on the divvying up of the loot.<br>
