Cowardice Lurkinglizard <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uottoemobeel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>OttoeMobeel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/8/01 12:03:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=796.topic&index=88>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dragon loot - opinions please.</span><hr size=1> as much as i would kill for dragon haste, or heck, even an fbss, i do hafta say that it sounds fair to me that bards get first dibs on white scales and first dibs along with warriors on red scales, and bards also have a chance at a great bard only instrument at each one, and hey, even the exciting possibility of an orb of tishan(be still, my beating heart), and it is i guess fair to leave bards outa the dragon haste, at least with this loot set up.<br>
<br>
now, i melee prolly 90% of my battles, but thats since in me and Tedy Bayers little bard/monk duo of butt kicking, i'm always hasting, and also snaring/slowing, which are both vocal songs, so i always have my weapons in unless i'm doing CC, in which case i usually just heal and buff between mezzing and charming, if i have the chance to even throw in the extra heal/buff.<br>
<br>
but even considering that, i think i would rather have one of the hardest parts of my epic, and prolly at least want a selos drum equally as much as a CoF, and oohh, the joy if an orb of tishan dropped.  so my point is that i could live without a roll on a cof or rbb if i have a chance for so many better things, and even tho my bard is my main, i am a man of a million alts, so i understand at least to some degree the plight of almost every class, and i would hate to be one of the main tank warriors on a naggy raid where one bard got a red scale, another bard got selos drum, and a third bard got a CoF, and then maybe a monk got a backpack.<br>
<br>
let me put that differently, i wouldn't &quot;hate&quot; to be a part of that raid, cuz i really do hope to enjoy the experience of slaying a dragon as much as any possible prize, and i also would love to see my peers and guild mates made stronger, but i definately would understand any ranger or warrior or &lt;fill in the blank class&gt; who was mad because they didn't barely get a chance at anything, while watching one class walk away with everything.<br>
<br>
gosh, every one of my posts today have been way to scatter brained, lacking in proper punctuation and grammer, and i think now is a good time to end this ramble-fest :-)<br>
<br>
Ottoe Mobeel<br>
37th lvl bard<br>
Harpers of Luclin<br>
